  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    io.micronaut.core.annotation.AnnotatedElement, io.micronaut.core.annotation.AnnotationMetadata, io.micronaut.core.annotation.AnnotationMetadataDelegate, io.micronaut.core.annotation.AnnotationMetadataProvider, io.micronaut.core.annotation.AnnotationSource, io.micronaut.core.naming.Named, io.micronaut.inject.ast.ArrayableClassElement, io.micronaut.inject.ast.ClassElement, io.micronaut.inject.ast.Element, io.micronaut.inject.ast.TypedElement

    @Internal
public class JavaClassElementExt
extends io.micronaut.annotation.processing.visitor.JavaClassElement
    A class element returning data from a TypeElement. Implementation note: [smell] this class needs to track changes to JavaClassElement. For example: JavaClassElement introduced JavaClassElement.arrayDimensions resulting in a processing bug in this library when this class didn't account for it in the constructor.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    James Kleeh, graemerocher, croudet
